[ctns_make id='gen_abs_prop_y_divides_x']

  [ctns_front style='font-size:150%;']
$$ \left| \frac xy \right| = \frac{|x|}{|y|}, $$ <br/> $$\footnotesize y \ne 0$$
  [/ctns_front]  

  [ctns_back style='font-size:150%;']
$$ \color{blue}{\left| \frac xy \right| = \frac{|x|}{|y| } ,} $$ <br/> $$\color{blue}{\footnotesize y \ne 0}$$
  [/ctns_back]  

  [ctns_frontspeak]
The absolute value of x divided by why equals the absolute of exx divided by the absolute value of why.
  [/ctns_frontspeak]  

  [ctns_backspeak]
The absolute value of x divided by why equals the absolute of exx divided by the absolute value of why, why equal to zero excepted.
  [/ctns_backspeak]  

[/ctns_make]
